How can you fall in love when you can’t even hold hands? Due to a childhood curse, anything that the Duke touches will die—which makes his flirty maid’s behavior all the more shocking! Is there a way for the Duke and his companions to somehow break the curse, or is he doomed to a life where love is forever out of his reach?
(Source: Funimation)

The third season of Log Horizon. It’s been a year since Shiroe and his friends were trapped in Akiba due to the Catastrophe. Their forging of the Round Table has brought order and prosperity to its people. But fracturing political alliances and the constant menace of the Genius monsters threaten to destabilize all they’ve fought for and built. Can faith be restored and they persevere, or is its destruction truly inevitable? (Source: Funimation)
Akuyaku Reijou desu ga, Shiawase ni Natte Misemasu wa!

Annuled engagements, "serves you right"s, condemnation events, doting, royalty, reincarnated heroines, banishment endings... it's fully loaded with all the charms of villainesses!! Despite all the Villainess' stories starting off in dire straits, in the end they're...all happy endings♪ A comicalization of popular villainess stories that were published on Shousetsuka ni Narou! An anthology of oneshots with happy endings!! Volume 1 Cover illustration: Maro 1. "The Villainess Will Obtain True Love" by Hoshino Soumei Author: Nekomata Doremi An annulled engagement at a graduation party?! 2. "The Tale of the Noble Girl who will go to a Monastery after her Engagement Annulment" by Sorakura SHIJIKI, Author: Yuuki Satoru Banishment after her younger sister steals her fiance?! 3. "I Will Definitely Get My Engagement Annulled! ~I will become a Villainess!" by Kuroe Yui, Author: Reiga Utsuho To break off her engagement, she harasses the daughter of a Baron?! 4. "Shall We Walk Hand in Hand Down the Flowery Path of Evil?" by Yamashiro Umeta, Author: Mafuyubi After her engagement is annulled, she gets married to a fat old baldy?! 5. "The Villainess Trifles with the Second Prince's First Love" by Oshitsuji Ei, Author: Mizuno Saaya After being condemned, the second prince appears before me... Volume 2 Cover illustration: Maro 1. "It's Been 10 Years Since You Asked to Break Off Our Engagement, If You Insist That Much, Let's Break It Off!" by Maro, Author: Yoshimura She's been told multiple times since they were young to break off the engagement?! 2. "The Villainess Laughs Innocently" by Oshitsuji Ei, Author: Yoruru A Condemnation Event after being called out to the rear garden?! 3. "The Art of Rebuilding a Nation Begins with a Broken Engagement!" by Kawano Akiko, Author: Hazuki The Prince has an affair with the Saintess and calls off his engagement?! 4. "You Were Set Up, You Know?" by Koyuki Iroha, Author: Yuki Yukiko At the graduation party, my older sister's engagement was broken?! 5. "The Villainess Exploded" by Nanso, Author: bouro The Villainess tells the Second Prince "Serves you right"?! 6. "I Reincarnated as a Villainess. Come Quickly, my Engagement Breaking Event" by Mochida Moo, Author: Kyouka The only ally the reincarnated Villainess has is the butler?!
Osananajimi ga Zettai ni Makenai Love Come

My childhood friend Shida Kuroha seems to have feelings for me. She lives next door, and is small and cute. With an outgoing character, she’s the caring Onee-san type, this being one of her greatest strengths.
…But, I already have my first love, the beautiful idol of our school, and the award-winning author high school girl, Kachi Shirokusa! Thinking about it rationally, I should have no chances with her, but, while walking home from school, she only talks to me, with a smile even! I might actually have a chance, don’t you think?!
Or so I thought, but then I heard that Shirokusa already has a boyfriend, and my life took a turn for the worse. I want to die. Why is it not me?! Even though she was my first love…As I was drowning in despair and depression, Kuroha whispered.
—If it’s that tough for you, then how about we get revenge? The best revenge ever, that is~

div.span: Turbulent Adventurers are Introverted, Observant, Feeling, Prospecting and Turbulent. They tend to have open minds, approaching life, new experiences, and people with grounded warmth.
Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Likely pragmatic and down-to-earth, with a strong focus on what is happening or very likely to happen.
Likely values emotional expression and sensitivity, prioritizing empathy, social harmony, and cooperation.
Likely very good at improvising and adapting. Tends to be flexible and values novelty above stability.
Likely self-conscious, sensitive to stress, success-driven, perfectionistic, and eager to improve.
